Support Engagement Standard Operating Procedure (SOP)

Version 1.0

Effective Date: 05/15/2023

1. Purpose:
   
   To outline the proper procedures to handle Spiceworks tickets.
   
2. Responsibilities:

   The technician must be alert of any new and ongoing ticket.
   
   Identify and assign the priority of a ticket.

   Be courteous and respectful.

   Document the process within the Spiceworks internal notes system.

   Make sure all issues are resolved before closing the ticket.


3. Definitions and Abbreviations:

   Data: Any and all things stored in the computer.
4. Procedure:
   
   Technicians are expected to follow the CompTIA troubleshooting methodology.

   a. Identify the problem.

   b. Establish a theory of probable cause.

   c. Test the theory to determine the cause.

   d. Establish a plan of action and implement the solution.

   e. Verify full system functionality and implement preventative measures.

   f. Document findings. 

5. Safety Considerations:

   
   Back up any data that may be lost in the process of troubleshooting. This includes system restore points, snapshots, or registry backups.

   Under the assumption that the system might be infected with malware, run a virus scan before and after procedures with Windows Defender and Malwarebytes.

   Make note of any password changes or user settings changes throughout the procedure.

6. Troubleshooting and Problem Solving:
   
   If the issue cannot be resolved in a timely manner, escalate the ticket to a higher level.

   Be open to any possible scenarios - the biggest problems can be solved with a simple answer.
7. References:
   
   https://www.comptia.org/blog/troubleshooting-methodology

   https://community.spiceworks.com/support/help-desk-cloud-edition/
8. Revision History:
   
   Version 1.0: Initial SOP created.
